              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " function is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server designed to calculate a prorated value based on a given date range. This function is used in scenarios where a value needs to be distributed proportionally over a period, such as calculating prorated charges or allocations."
